  "rules": [],
  "notes": "GDCC Instruction Type refers to the original trigger for the update i.e. (I) initial data, (U) update, (P) Remittance Processor update to previous Supplier, (R) Refresh, (C) Change of Supply event, (E) Change of Supply following an Erroneous Registration, (T) Provision of revised charging information to Erroneously Registered Supplier, or (D) Default Bill Payer only.Though each address line is optional, when an address is to be updated using this flow the entire address must be included in the flow, an update to an individual line within an address will require the entire address to be sent.Where an D0325 is received by the GD Licensee, an D0341 response should always be generated."
